09/07/2007
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Defence Minister Dragan Sutanovac has decided to ban war crimes indictees from accessing military facilities.
According to a statement Sunday (July 8th), the move is part of the new government drive's to locate and bring all remaining fugitives to justice.
Military police have been ordered to search all buildings, from the smallest outposts to the largest barracks.
In other news, in an interview for RTS on Sunday, Danish Foreign Minister Per Stig Moeller said Serbia could initial a Stabilisation and Association Agreement with the EU in October or November, but due to procedural issues, would not be able to officially seal the accord by the end of this year.
He said the political part of the accord could be completed during the next round of talks, this month.
(Blic - 09/07/07;
Tanjug, Beta, RTS - 08/07/07)
